ur.com/VYnelJu.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dUB8dEA.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PQ0cVVw.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XAydPka</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[UncleSlam123]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Parenting is hard but people make it so much harder</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7KIswiT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Cff7C2d.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oeFSpyi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AKR1yc0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zZEfoOh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ii5R8OC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V1wYt2q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My wife had to go to another state for several days after a sudden family death. I stayed home with our 4 kids due to school and sports obligations (our kids didn't really know the person). My wife runs her own business, and I get a buttload of PTO at work, so I am also covering her daycare for 2 days (yes, the parents are cool with this).
I have gotten so many comments about what a good father I am for "babysitting" the kids and watching her daycare from other mothers because their husbands wouldn't do the same and I'm just annoyed and couldnt decide which meme format I wanted to express that frustration lol. 
I get the daycare part, but you don't babysit your own kids. It's called parenting.
I'm not saying that it's easy because it's not. I've always told my wife that my job is a cakewalk compared to her job. My neck and feet are sore after just one day (and I'm a nurse!)

Thank you void for listening. They're all good voids, Bront</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7KIswiT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SarcasticRN]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>When works too much, I hope you have someone like this persons husband! Lol</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9IWa8d9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/C5DPtzQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/smC9DAX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9IWa8d9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DumpingSh1tandBeingKind2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Love the honesty from Miss USA 1997</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/R0ABHOM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vtGTlbb.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/R0ABHOM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[kidfromOKwiththetuckfromMB]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>